  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For the mouth of the wicked and the mouth of the deceitful - literally, \"The mouth of wickedness, and the mouth of deceit.\" This acquaints us with the nature of the wrong which had been done him. It was slander; undeserved reproach.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Are opened against me - Margin, \"have opened;\" that is, have opened themselves.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They have spoken against me with a lying tongue - They have accused me of things which are not true; they have made false charges against me. David, as has not been uncommon with good people, was called repeatedly to this trial. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "They have spoken against me with a lying tongue - They have accused me of things which are not true; they have made false charges against me. David, as has not been uncommon with good people, was called repeatedly to this trial. ",
            "children": []
          },
